main event: A compressor operator working on the Lark Tunnel in Utah reported sighting an unidentified aerial object on October 17, 1950.
interesting points: The object initially appeared as a long, thin line of fire crossing the sky at high speed.
The object then thickened and closed in on itself at the front and rear, with the main body swaying in the air before fading out completely.
The witness was unsure which agency to report the sighting to.
The report mentions that the 115th CIC Detachment received the information and forwarded it, but no further investigation was initiated.
The report is heavily redacted, with many details about the object and the sighting obscured.
